cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.PL 

The paper deals with the problem of learning a non-deterministic probabilistic system, which is a topic that falls under the broad area of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of state-space partitioning and active learning also suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the application of the proposed algorithms to an automated verification framework for probabilistic systems suggests a connection to programming languages (cs.PL).
